        <num>CC 3067</num>
        <heading>3067.  Permissible variations</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3067.  Permissible variations
A surety is not liable for a sum in excess of that expressly stated in his contract.  A legal suretyship may contain terms more favorable to the creditor than those required by the law or order pursuant to which it is given, but it may not provide for a time longer than is provided by law for bringing an action against the surety.</p>
        </content>
